    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.18.1"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">1</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">CHICAGO ∙ BOSTON ∙ ATLANTA ∙ DALLAS ∙ SAN FRANCISCO ∙ LONDON ∙ TORONTO ∙ BOMBAY ∙ CALCUTTA ∙ MADRAS ∙ MELBOURNE ∙ SHANGHAI ∙ MAN<unclear reason="missing" cert="high">ILA</unclear>
                
                    THE MACMILLAN COMPANY
                
                    CABLE ADDRESS
                    PACHAMAC NEW YORK</hi>
                
                    <hi rend="italics">Publishers</hi>
                
                    <hi rend="caps">TELEPHONE 
                    ALGONQUIN 4-2100
                
                    SIXTY ∙ FIFTH AVENUE ∙ NEW YORK
                
                    GEORGE P. BRETT JR., PRESIDENT
                    L.J. LUCAS, SECRETARY
                    R.M. BRETT, TREASURER
                
                    H.S. LATHAM, VICE PRESIDENT
                    IN CHARGE OF ALL <unclear>TRADE</unclear> DEPARTMENTS
                    A.H. NELSON VICE PRESIDENT
                    IN CHARGE OF ALL EDUCATIONAL DEPARTMENTS</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>March 2, 1938</dateline>
                
                    
                    <salute>My dear Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Thank you for your letter. We shall, of course, be very glad to waive the motion picture rights in any of your books upon request to do so. I suppose it might just as well be allowed to stand as it is at present,with the understanding that should you come to any final conclusion with any motion picture copany we would give you all motion picture rights.</p>
                
                <p>I am delighted to hear that you are getting along nicely with <hi rend="caps">JED SMITH</hi>.</p>
                
                <p>I can't tell you what pleasant memories I have of the delightful evening I spent with you and your family. It was a high spot in my Southern trip.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Cordially yours,</salute>
                    <signed>H.S. Latham</signed>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>St. Louis Post-Dispatch</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>St. Louis, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <note>HSL/mc</note>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
